(234, 1, '2013-03-22 23:07:54', '2013-03-23 04:07:54', 'When clients ask me for suggestions on how to market themselves and their websites, the number one answer I have is to start blogging. Blogging doesnt need to be a rant about politics or an anonymous expos about your personal life. Literally, blogging is a web-log; meaning, content that is published online, in chronological order. If you have an expertise and own a business, you should be writing about the work you do. Consider it a part of your portfolio. Dont just show potential customers you can do the work; explain how you do it, why you do it, and why they need to spend the money hiring you to do it for them.\r\n\r\nA blog is a great way to tap into your creativity, too. Sometimes we get stuck and start to feel like one-trick-ponies. Take the time to think about all the knowledge youve accumulated in order to get where you are today. How many paths led you to this point in your life? If youre like me, you love to plan. Youre focused and determined and have a clear vision of what you want to accomplish. But despite my planning, I know better than anyone how opportunities have presented themselves to me in unexpected ways. These opportunities are how we grow and learn and become great at what we do. They keep us motivated and inspire us, and they keep us open-minded and flexible. What a great thing to write about!\r\n\r\nStill not convinced you should be blogging? Consider some of these reasons:\r\n\r\n<h2>Fresh Content</h2>\r\nWebsites with new and fresh content are important for Search Engine Optimization. No one knows for sure what the algorithm is for a high Google ranking, but just like your FICO score, we all know what we have to do to maintain good credit. Websites are no different. Content that is updated regularly is indexed by search engines more often, and this can only help your page rank. Blogging accomplishes this beautifully, especially if you are a frequent blogger.\r\n<h2>Diversity</h2>\r\nWhen you get creative with your writing, consider the audience youll attract. For example, a dog-walker might blog about pet first aid, local dog parks, and the best healthy treats for their furry clients. All great blogging topics for a dog-walker! But how does he or she keep a blog diverse to attract a new audience, and still stay on topic? In a place like Minnesota where we have dramatic shifts in the weather, a blog about weather related gear would be perfect! Write about how a certain coat keeps you warm enough to spend time outside in the winter, or about the layers that can wick moisture and protect you from the sun in the summer. An entirely new audience could find your blog based on these topics, and as a result you could earn new clients.\r\n<h2>Demonstrable Intelligence</h2>\r\nSelf promotion being one of the hardest things we do, this is no time to be shy. If youre running a business you need to tell people you are smart and articulate. Can you think of a better way to do that than with a blog? This is your chance to say Heres what I can do for you! Start telling people about your ideas and how hard you work by letting them read what you have to say. Its implied that you started your endeavor because you knew you had something to offer. But you cant stop there! Keep going! When you blog frequently about your business, industry, art, and passion, there can be no question that youre the right person for the job.\r\n<h2>Teaching</h2>\r\nPeople love tutorials; they love to learn and to follow along. And why wouldnt they? What is the first thing you do when you have a question or need to learn about something? Do you Google it like the rest of the free world? Whether you write it out; step by step, or you record a video for YouTube, start teaching people how to do things and youll build an audience in no time. Its okay to give away a little something for free. Save the complicated stuff for your paying customers, and in the meantime youll grow a sizable following that can easily turn into people who will pay you for work.\r\n\r\nIf youre already blogging, tell me why in the comments below. What do you blog about? How has it helped your business? If you arent blogging but want to start and need help developing an idea, let us know about that, too. Happy blogging!', 'Why aren''t you blogging?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'why-arent-you-blogging', '', '', '2014-10-19 12:56:16', '2014-10-19 19:56:16', '', 0, 'http://angelajholden.com/ajh/?p=234', 0, 'post', '', 0),
