(1506, 1, '2014-10-15 08:23:08', '2014-10-15 15:23:08', 'Managing content is a big deal if you have a website or use social media to promote anything. Businesses and individuals are using things like Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn as marketing tools and a way to brand themselves, their products, or any interest theyre sharing with the world.\r\n\r\nAs a web designer and someone who specializes in development for the largest content management system on the web, WordPress, I am doing myself and my clients a disservice by not offering content strategy coaching. Websites are powerful marketing tools, but wont do you any good without a plan. So what is content strategy and what does it mean to have it?\r\n\r\nFirst lets define strategy. A quick Google search brings me to the Wikipedia page on strategy and a definition with Greek roots:  a high level plan to achieve one or more goals under conditions of uncertainty. This definitions origin is militaristic, but I think it sums up the internet perfectly.\r\n\r\nI think the key words here are goals and uncertainty. Its understood that the market, economy, and nature of your business can change on a dime, so how to you prepare yourself for that uncertainty? You set goals. With a website and the free or cheap marketing opportunities that come with social media, you have an audience at your fingertips thats waiting to hear from you. And where theres an audience, theres a market.\r\n<h2>A Website</h2>\r\nWhether its WordPress, Drupal, Joomla, or any one of the hundreds of content management systems, you have a platform at your fingertips to produce new content.\r\n<h3>Start Strategizing</h3>\r\nSet a Goal. Make a decision about how often, and how much, content you will produce for your website. Frequent blogging is usually 2-3 times a week. Start with one article a week at roughly 200-300 words each to get into the habit. Yes, its a habit youll need to develop.\r\n<h3>What kind of content?</h3>\r\nBlogging is best. Static content, like your About page, typically doesnt change. A blog is timely information about you or your business. It shouldnt necessarily be personal in nature, either. It should be related to what you do, but if your brand is you, then by all means include it, just be mindful of oversharing. Write tutorials, post videos of yourself working, and take lots of pictures. This all counts as content, and you should post it as often as possible.\r\n<h2>Social Media</h2>\r\nI use Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn, but admittedly I prefer Facebook, so thats where I spend the majority of my time. For the purpose of this article, Facebook will be my primary example. But no matter what you use, social media must be a part of your content strategy.\r\n\r\nGoogle the question How many people use Facebook? and youll come up with a range of answers. As of this writing, it seems to be roughly 1.3 billion people worldwide, which makes it the second most visited website in the world after Google.\r\n<h3>Start a Facebook business page and invite all of your friends to like it.</h3>\r\nUse that page to LIKE things related to your business or interest, and now you have a feed of status updates related just to your page. You can LIKE those updates as your page, and you can SHARE them on your pages timeline. This behavior is exactly like your personal profile, except its only related to your page and your business.\r\n<h3>Facebooks real power lies in advertising.</h3>\r\nI didnt fully understand this until recently, but dont forget what I said earlier in this article; where theres an audience, theres a market. If you cant reach beyond your friends, how do you ever grow your audience for a Facebook business page? Take out an ad.\r\n<h3>Free &amp; Cheap Advertising</h3>\r\nIf you have a website, check with your website host to see if you have any free advertising credits. This is how I got started. I use <a href="http://fatcow.com" target="_blank">fatcow.com</a> to register my domains and had a $50 Facebook ad credit just for opening an account. Through my own friends I was able to get just over 50 LIKES to my page, but with that credit spread out over 10 days, at just $5 a day, I grew my audience to over 100 new LIKES. Now I have a pool of people, and their friends, to reach.\r\n<h3>Now that you have an audience, whats your strategy?</h3>\r\nFacebook has an algorithm to determine who sees what you post on your page. So, just because someone LIKES your page doesnt mean that your updates are front and center in their feed. Like good SEO, the most engaging content is going to be organic, sincere, and consistent. Each time you post an article to your blog, share it on your page. Use good images, whether you take them yourself or you buy them from a place like Dollar Photo Club, and give your audience something substantive. You should do this frequently; almost every day.\r\n\r\nMost of us spend at least an hour or more a day on various social media outlets, so make marketing and promotion a daily part of your routine. Bottom line: Sharing content you find is in and of itself, content strategy. It also shows your audience that youre paying attention to whats happening in the world around you, and staying current in your field.\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\nBlogging and using social media are just the tip of the iceberg to your overall content strategy. In future articles Ill dive deeper to help you get a better understanding of managing the content on your website with the power of taxonomy, inventories, and audits, and Ill give you resources to better understand the marketing opportunities available in social media.\r\n\r\nTo get started with your own content strategy, start setting goals about the kind of content youll create, and how often youll create it. Then decide where youre going to share it, and how youll grow that audience. Then you can start to follow people and organizations similar to yours and share their content as well.', 'What is Content Strategy?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-content-strategy', '', '', '2014-10-19 12:56:16', '2014-10-19 19:56:16', '', 0, 'http://angelajholden.com/?p=1506', 0, 'post', '', 0),
